{\plain Logan, Utah, September 30, 1934.\par
}{\plain \par
}{\plain A patriarchal blessing given by Harvey Sessions, Patriarch, upon the head of Maria Elizabeth 
Waite Jorgensen, daughter of Levi Joseph Waite, and Maria Pheonix Waite, born December 13, 
1884, at Dayton, Idaho. \par
}{\plain \par
}{\plain Sister Maria Elizabeth Waite Jorgensen:\par
}{\plain \par
}{\plain \tab In the authority of the Holy Melchizedek Priesthood and in the name of Jesus Christ I lay 
my hands upon your head to give unto you a patriarchal blessing. Father in heaven draw near 
unto us upon this occasion for this thy handmaiden has come to me as thy servant desiring that 
she may have a blessing, and dictate to me the blessing Thou has in store for her. \par
}{\plain \tab Dear sister thou art a chosen vessel in the eyes of God our Father. You rifled your first 
estate in the spirit world with honor and have been permitted to come to earth in this day and age 
when the gospel has come to earth, and you have striven to keep the commandments of God. \par
}{\plain \tab You are a mother in Israel and the Lord loves you for you have been faithful in that line. 
You have lived in peace with your husband, and your family has learned to love you. They have 
been born under the new and everlasting covenant and they will be an honor to you, and your 
heart will rejoice as it has from childhood. Your posterity will be numbered among the faithful 
ones in the earth. They will be God-fearing men and women and defend the principles of eternal 
truth, and God will pour out His spirit upon them. \par
}{\plain \tab Be of good cheer for you are of F.phraim through the loins of Joseph, and every blessing 
God has promised to his handmaidens you are entitled to, and through your faith and integrity He 
will bless you. Peace will whisper to your heart and joy will fill your soul, arid you will be one 
who all mankind will look to as one of the noble daughters of God. I bless you with every 
blessing which is in store for His faithful daughters. Continue your faithful labors and live near 
to Him; make Him your friend and you will be able to continue your work. \par
}{\plain \tab I seal you up against the power of the destroyer and pray God you will have strength to 
resist the temptations as they come to you through life, and you will know God has hoard your 
prayers when trials and troubles cone to you but you will be comforted and you will know He is 
your friend. \par
}{\plain \tab Be humble; be prayerful and faithful, and with your husband you will journey together 
through life. I bless you with health and strength that you will live long upon the earth and your 
children and children\'92s children for I bless you with a large posterity. \par
}{\plain \tab I seal you up to come forth in the morning of the first resurrection clothed with glory, 
immortality and eternal life, and I do it in the name of Jesus Christ and as a patriarch, Amen. \par
}{\plain \par
}\pard \qr\sl0 
{\plain Harvey Sessions, Patriarch\par
}\pard \sl0 
{\plain Recorded by Lucy Shaw\par
